# melipolibre-api

Meliponiculture is the study and practice of keeping and breeding stingless bees, also known as meliponines. These bees are native to tropical and subtropical regions and are known for their docility and importance as pollinators.

melipolibre-api is an API designed to help developers build applications for meliponiculture. It's written in Python and uses Redis as its primary data store.

## Installation

To install melipolibre-api, you'll need to first install all of its dependencies. This can be done by running the following command:

pip install -r requirements.txt

Once all of the dependencies are installed, you'll be ready to use the API in your application.


## Run
flask run


## Contributing
We welcome contributions to melipolibre-api. If you find a bug or have an idea for a new feature, please open an issue or a pull request.

